headline: Samsung’s Chip Profit Soars After AI Fuels Demand for Memory
summary: The unit, which competes with SK Hynix Inc. and US-based Micron Technology Inc., said it will focus next year on mass production of the next generation of high-bandwidth memory or HBM4 — designed to work in tandem with AI accelerators from Nvidia Corp. The company echoed SK Hynix’s prediction that a spending spree in artificial intelligence will persist this quarter and into next year.  Its shares climbed 3.6% in Seoul during the regular session.
